# Mojo Code Documentation

## Public functions

Non-obvious public functions and exported entrypoints: doc comment with purpose, parameter meaning, return/error behavior.

Short obvious helpers may stay undocumented if name and types are sufficient.

## Struct fields

Named struct fields that are not self-explanatory: inline comment or doc — semantics, units, valid ranges, opaque vs internal id.

## Enums and aliases

Domain enums and type aliases: one-line comment on what each variant/alias means when not obvious from the name.

## Module layout (soft guide)

- Top: imports, public API, types, constants.
- Bottom or near use: private helpers that serve specific functions above.
- Do not reorder entire files for aesthetics only; apply on new edits where it helps the next reader.
